I've revised the plan based on your round-0 findings. Summary of changes:
1. Auth: switched to plain HTTP (matches existing reference soft-isolation posture; Gitea is in-network only). Added explicit eden-user-create-with-password step + idempotent password update on re-run. Documented the soft-boundary widening alongside DooD §7.
2. Integrator rollback: now an explicit four-step ladder: local create_ref → remote push_ref → store.integrate_trial → on store failure, remote delete_ref + local delete_ref. Added GitRepo.delete_remote_ref as a fourth new operation. Trial.integrated emits AFTER step 3 (committed-and-published).
3. Crash recovery: startup-time reconciliation walks BOTH work/* AND trial/* local refs and prunes orphans (those without remote backing). Added per-operation read-before-write/read-before-display fetch policy for long-lived clones (orchestrator + web-ui).
4. Tests: replaced argv-only credential test with a real http.server roundtrip via the helper script. Added explicit Integrator.integrate() failure-mode tests (push race, store failure post-push, compensating-delete failure). Smoke now asserts via git ls-remote against the actual Gitea remote.
5. Sequencing: committed to option (a). setup-experiment now brings Gitea up + provisions before printing operator next-steps. Added new §F-T 'Cutover blast-radius inventory' with concrete file counts.

Please re-review.
