     1	# Phase 10d follow-up B — Gitea as the workers' git remote
     2	
     3	## Context
     4	
     5	Chunks 10b/10c shipped a Compose stack where Gitea runs but is
     6	idle. Workers (orchestrator's integrator + the implementer host
     7	across both subprocess-mode wrappers) all read and write through
     8	the **shared `eden-bare-repo` named volume**. That works for a
     9	single-host reference deployment but doesn't reflect the
    10	multi-host topology spec chapter 06 contemplates: each worker
    11	should own a private working copy and exchange refs with a
    12	**central git remote** that's the sole source of truth.
    13	
    14	This sub-chunk closes that delta. Workers stop touching the shared
    15	bare-repo volume; they `git fetch` / `git push` against Gitea over
    16	HTTPS instead. The orchestrator's integrator does the same for
    17	`trial/*` promotion. setup-experiment provisions Gitea (admin,
    18	HTTPS-Basic credentials, repo creation, seed push).
    19	
    20	Direction confirmed with the user before drafting:
    21	
    22	- **A. Full cutover** — no shared bare-repo fallback. Cleaner
    23	  blast radius; the volume gets removed.
    24	- **B. HTTPS Basic auth** via per-experiment credential helper —
    25	  matches the existing reference soft-isolation posture.
    26	- **C. Extend `eden_git.GitRepo` with a remote-aware variant** —
    27	  `GitRepo` itself stays additive; existing `create_ref` and
    28	  related local ops keep working for in-process tests, plus a
    29	  new `push_ref` and `fetch_ref` (and a few helpers) on top.
    30	
    31	## Design
    32	
    33	### D.1 Topology after cutover
    34	
    35	Before:
    36	
    37	```
    38	            ┌──────────────────────┐
    39	            │  eden-bare-repo vol  │ ←── orchestrator/integrator
    40	            │  (shared, writable)  │ ←── implementer-host
    41	            └──────────────────────┘ ←── evaluator-host (read-only)
    42	```
    43	
    44	After:
    45	
    46	```
    47	                    ┌─────────────┐
    48	                    │   Gitea     │
    49	                    │   HTTPS     │   <─── source of truth
    50	                    └─────────────┘
    51	                  fetch │ ▲ push
    52	            ┌───────────┘ │ └───────────┐
    53	       ┌────▼────┐  ┌─────▼────┐  ┌─────▼────┐
    54	       │ implem. │  │ integ.   │  │ eval.    │
    55	       │ (clone) │  │ (clone)  │  │ (clone)  │
    56	       └─────────┘  └──────────┘  └──────────┘
    57	```
    58	
    59	Each role-host container holds a **private clone** under
    60	`/var/lib/eden/repo` (still bind-mounted for persistence, but the
    61	volume is per-service, not shared). The clone is initialized at
    62	host startup from Gitea: clean state on first boot, recovered
    63	on restart.
    64	
    65	### D.2 `eden_git.GitRepo` extensions
    66	
    67	Three new public methods (all dispatch through the existing
    68	`subprocess.run(["git", ...])` plumbing — no shellouts to a new
    69	binary, no new dependency):
    70	
    71	- `clone_from(*, url: str, dest: Path, credential_helper: str | None) -> GitRepo`
    72	  — `git clone --bare` (for the integrator) or `git clone`
    73	  (for implementer/evaluator). When `credential_helper` is set,
    74	  threads it through `git -c credential.helper=<…>` so HTTPS
    75	  Basic creds don't have to land in `~/.git-credentials`.
    76	- `push_ref(ref: str, expected_old_sha: str | None) -> None` —
    77	  `git push origin <ref>` with `--force-with-lease=<ref>:<sha>`
    78	  when `expected_old_sha` is supplied. Maps daemon-side rejections
    79	  to the same `RefRefused` exception `create_ref` raises today,
    80	  so call sites stay structurally identical.
    81	- `fetch_ref(ref: str) -> str | None` — `git fetch origin
    82	  <ref>:<ref>` with `--prune=false`; returns the fetched SHA.
    83	  Used by the integrator to re-read `work/*` and `trial/*` it
    84	  doesn't have locally.
    85	
    86	`create_ref` / `update_ref` / `delete_ref` stay on the local repo;
    87	the integrator and implementer call `push_ref` immediately after
    88	the local ref-write to publish. This keeps the existing local
    89	discipline (CAS via zero-oid on create, expected-old-sha on update)
    90	intact, and adds publication as a strictly-additive step.
    91	
    92	### D.3 Auth flow — HTTP Basic via per-experiment credential helper
    93	
    94	The reference Gitea is exposed on plain HTTP inside the compose
    95	network (no TLS). That matches the existing soft-isolation
    96	posture documented in §7 of
    97	[`spec/v0/reference-bindings/worker-host-subprocess.md`](../../spec/v0/reference-bindings/worker-host-subprocess.md):
    98	the reference deployment trades isolation for operational
    99	simplicity, and a hardened deployment substitutes a TLS-fronted
   100	Gitea behind the same `git://` URL. We document this caveat
   101	alongside the existing DooD soft boundary; the secret-handling
   102	boundary widens by exactly one channel (now the eden user's
   103	Gitea password is also visible to anyone with daemon access).
   104	
   105	setup-experiment.sh, after starting Gitea + waiting for healthy:
   106	
   107	1. Generate a per-experiment password `GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD`
   108	   (32 hex bytes; same shape as other reference secrets).
   109	2. Provision the eden user (idempotent — first checks via
   110	   `gitea admin user list`):
   111	
   112	   ```bash
   113	   docker compose exec -T gitea gitea admin user create \
   114	       --username eden \
   115	       --password "${GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD}" \
   116	       --email eden@invalid \
   117	       --admin
   118	   ```
   119	
   120	   Re-running with a different password updates the existing
   121	   user (`gitea admin user change-password`) so re-runs of
   122	   setup-experiment with new env files don't desync.
   123	3. Generate a per-experiment access token (used only by
   124	   setup-experiment for repo creation, NOT by workers; workers
   125	   use Basic auth):
   126	
   127	   ```bash
   128	   curl -fsS -u "eden:${GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD}" \
   129	       -X POST http://localhost:${GITEA_HOST_PORT}/api/v1/users/eden/tokens \
   130	       -d '{"name":"setup","scopes":["write:repository"]}'
   131	   ```
   132	4. Create the repo `eden/<EXPERIMENT_ID>.git` via
   133	   `POST /api/v1/user/repos` (idempotent — handle 409).
   134	5. Write the **credential-helper script** to a host-side path
   135	   `${COMPOSE_DIR}/.gitea-creds-${EXPERIMENT_ID}/credential-helper.sh`,
   136	   substituting the password into a template. The script:
   137	
   138	   ```sh
   139	   #!/bin/sh
   140	   case "$1" in
   141	     get)
   142	       cat <<EOF
   143	   username=eden
   144	   password=__GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD__
   145	   EOF
   146	       ;;
   147	   esac
   148	   ```
   149	
   150	   Mode 0755. Mounted read-only into every worker host container
   151	   at `/etc/eden/credential-helper.sh`.
   152	
   153	Workers configure git to use the helper via repo-local config
   154	written at clone time (NOT global config — keeps the secret out
   155	of the worker's home dir):
   156	
   157	```bash
   158	git -c credential.helper="/etc/eden/credential-helper.sh" \
   159	    -c http.extraHeader="" \
   160	    clone http://gitea:3000/eden/<EXPERIMENT_ID>.git \
   161	    /var/lib/eden/repo
   162	git -C /var/lib/eden/repo config credential.helper \
   163	    "/etc/eden/credential-helper.sh"
   164	```
   165	
   166	Subsequent `git fetch` / `git push` invocations from that repo
   167	pick up the helper automatically. The chunk-10d-followup-A
   168	soft-boundary caveat (§7) is extended to cover this: the eden
   169	user's Gitea password is on the host filesystem at
   170	`${COMPOSE_DIR}/.gitea-creds-<id>/credential-helper.sh` mode 0755,
   171	readable by anyone on the host and (under DooD) by any
   172	concurrent `*_command`.
   173	
   174	### D.4 setup-experiment.sh sequencing — option (a) selected
   175	
   176	`setup-experiment.sh` already runs the bare-repo seed step
   177	synchronously via `compose run --rm --no-deps eden-repo-init`.
   178	This sub-chunk extends that pattern: setup-experiment now also
   179	**brings Gitea up** synchronously (before the rest of the stack)
   180	and provisions it before writing the operator's next-step
   181	instructions. No deferred work in the operator's own
   182	`compose up`.
   183	
   184	Concrete sequence (replaces the current "seed bare repo, write
   185	.env, exit" flow):
   186	
   187	1. Generate / preserve all secrets (existing flow), including
   188	   the new `GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD`.
   189	2. Write the partial `.env` (without `EDEN_BASE_COMMIT_SHA` —
   190	   filled in step 7).
   191	3. **Bring Gitea up:**
   192	   `docker compose --env-file "$ENV_FILE" up -d --wait gitea`
   193	   (uses Gitea's existing healthcheck).
   194	4. **Provision Gitea** per §D.3 (eden user, access token, repo).
   195	5. **Write the credential-helper script** under
   196	   `${COMPOSE_DIR}/.gitea-creds-${EXPERIMENT_ID}/`.
   197	6. **Seed + push** via `compose run --rm --no-deps eden-repo-init`,
   198	   which now takes a `--push-to <url>` flag and pushes the seed
   199	   commit to Gitea after creating the local bare repo.
   200	7. Capture the seed SHA, replace the `.env` placeholder
   201	   (existing pattern).
   202	8. Print operator next-steps (existing — `compose up -d --wait`).
   203	
   204	The shared `eden-bare-repo` volume is removed from `compose.yaml`
   205	in the cutover; `eden-repo-init` keeps writing to it locally only
   206	so the seed-and-push step is self-contained, then the volume is
   207	discarded by the existing `compose down -v` posture.
   208	
   209	**Idempotency:** all four provisioning operations (user create,
   210	token mint, repo create, ref push) are idempotent. Re-running
   211	setup-experiment with the same env file is a no-op for Gitea
   212	state. Re-running with a NEW env file (different
   213	`GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD`) updates the user's password via
   214	`gitea admin user change-password`.
   215	
   216	### D.5 Per-service compose changes
   217	
   218	Each worker host gains:
   219	
   220	- A *private* named volume for its clone:
   221	  `eden-implementer-repo`, `eden-evaluator-repo`,
   222	  `eden-orchestrator-repo` (no shared `eden-bare-repo` anymore).
   223	- The credential-helper script bind-mounted RO at
   224	  `/etc/eden/credential-helper.sh`.
   225	- A new `--gitea-url <https-url>` CLI flag on each host.
   226	
   227	Each worker host's startup logic:
   228	
   229	1. If `/var/lib/eden/repo` is not yet a git repo, `clone_from`
   230	   from Gitea (use `--bare` for the orchestrator/integrator and
   231	   the web-ui's implementer module; non-bare otherwise so
   232	   worktrees can be added).
   233	2. Otherwise, `git fetch origin '+refs/heads/*:refs/heads/*'` to
   234	   refresh ALL local heads to match remote.
   235	3. **Reconcile local-only refs.** Walk every local `work/*` and
   236	   `trial/*` ref. For each, `git ls-remote origin <ref>` —
   237	   if the remote doesn't have it, `delete_ref` locally (it's an
   238	   orphan from a pre-crash run). This handles both the
   239	   §D.7-implementer crash window AND the §D.6-step-4a-failed
   240	   case from a prior integrator crash.
   241	4. Enter the normal poll loop.
   242	
   243	**Per-operation freshness for long-lived clones.** The orchestrator
   244	loop and the web-ui's admin/implementer modules are long-lived;
   245	remote refs change under their feet between the startup fetch and
   246	the next operation. Two policies:
   247	
   248	- **Read-before-write:** any service path that's about to write a
   249	  ref via `repo.create_ref` first runs `git fetch origin <ref>`
   250	  to refresh its local view. This keeps `--force-with-lease`'s
   251	  expected-old-sha aligned with the remote.
   252	- **Read-before-display:** the web-ui admin work-refs GC page
   253	  (chunk-9e) runs `git fetch origin '+refs/heads/work/*:refs/heads/work/*'`
   254	  on every GET so the operator's view matches the remote. The
   255	  per-op fetch budget here is one HTTP roundtrip + a small ref
   256	  list, well under 100ms in the reference deployment.
   257	
   258	Failure mode: if Gitea is unreachable at startup, the host exits
   259	non-zero and compose's `restart: on-failure` (existing posture)
   260	retries until healthy. Mid-operation Gitea unreachability raises
   261	`GitTransportError` from `eden_git`; service-level handlers catch
   262	it and submit `status="error"` for the in-flight task.
   263	
   264	### D.6 Integrator (orchestrator) changes — explicit four-step flow
   265	
   266	The current integrator at
   267	[`reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py`](../../reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py)
   268	does (chapter 6 §3.2 / §3.4):
   269	
   270	```text
   271	1. local create_ref     # CAS-guarded
   272	2. store.integrate_trial
   273	3. on store failure: local delete_ref (compensating)
   274	```
   275	
   276	After this sub-chunk, the flow becomes a literal four-step
   277	publish-then-commit-then-rollback ladder:
   278	
   279	```text
   280	1. local create_ref           # CAS-guarded local
   281	2. remote push_ref            # publish to Gitea (force-with-lease)
   282	3. store.integrate_trial      # writes trial_commit_sha + trial.integrated
   283	4. on store failure:
   284	   4a. remote delete_ref      # compensating remote delete
   285	   4b. local delete_ref       # compensating local delete
   286	```
   287	
   288	The new step 4a — **remote compensating delete** — is load-bearing
   289	under chapter 6 §3.4: leaving `trial/*` on Gitea without the
   290	matching `trial.integrated` event in the store is a protocol
   291	violation, because the next replay of the event log would see a
   292	ref that no event explains. We MUST run step 4a before step 4b
   293	so a re-tried integration sees a clean Gitea slate.
   294	
   295	`GitRepo` therefore needs a fourth new method:
   296	
   297	- `delete_remote_ref(ref: str, expected_sha: str | None) -> None`
   298	  — `git push origin --delete <ref>` with a CAS guard via
   299	  `--force-with-lease=<ref>:<sha>`. If the remote ref has
   300	  diverged (someone else integrated a different commit on the
   301	  same trial id), raise `RefRefused` and let the caller decide.
   302	
   303	If step 2 fails (push rejected — concurrent integrator won
   304	the race), only step 1's local ref exists; we run step 4b
   305	(local delete) and skip 4a. If step 3 fails after step 2
   306	succeeded, we run BOTH 4a and 4b. If step 4a itself fails (Gitea
   307	unreachable), we log a critical-severity diagnostic and leave
   308	the local ref in place — the next integrator startup's
   309	fetch-and-reconcile pass (§D.7c below) cleans up.
   310	
   311	**Important:** `trial.integrated` is emitted by step 3 (atomically
   312	with the trial's `trial_commit_sha` write). Step 1 alone does NOT
   313	emit anything — only the *committed-and-published* ref counts.
   314	This preserves chapter 5 §2.2's "events emit only on committed
   315	state changes."
   316	
   317	### D.7 Implementer changes
   318	
   319	The implementer's existing flow per [chapter 03 §3.2](../../spec/v0/03-roles.md):
   320	
   321	```text
   322	1. Store.create_trial(status="starting")
   323	2. git worktree add <path> <parent>
   324	3. <user command writes commits>
   325	4. repo.create_ref("refs/heads/work/<…>", commit_sha)
   326	5. Store.submit(...)
   327	```
   328	
   329	becomes:
   330	
   331	```text
   332	1. Store.create_trial(status="starting")
   333	2. git worktree add <path> <parent>      # local
   334	3. <user command writes commits>
   335	4. repo.create_ref("refs/heads/work/<…>")  # local
   336	5. repo.push_ref("refs/heads/work/<…>")    # publish to Gitea
   337	6. Store.submit(...)
   338	```
   339	
   340	The submit's `commit_sha` is the local SHA that we just pushed.
   341	If push fails, we roll back the local ref (so the trial doesn't
   342	linger as a "starting" trial that references a non-published
   343	commit) and submit `status="error"`.
   344	
   345	### D.8 Evaluator changes
   346	
   347	The evaluator currently does `git worktree add <path>
   348	<trial.commit_sha>`. After cutover it must `git fetch
   349	origin trial/<id>` first so the local clone has the trial
   350	commit. The chapter-3 contract is unchanged; only the local
   351	fetch is added. Evaluator never pushes.
   352	
   353	### D.9 What does NOT change
   354	
   355	- Spec chapters 03 / 04 / 06 — the role contracts and integrator
   356	  invariants are silent on whether the workers share storage or
   357	  use a remote. Both fit the existing prose.
   358	- The `Store` Protocol — entirely separate from git.
   359	- The chunk-10d JSON-line `*_command` protocol — unchanged.
   360	- `eden-runtime:dev` and the experiment image — git is already
   361	  installed.
   362	
