 succeeded in 0ms:
   420	
   421	- `GitRepo.clone_from(url=file://…, dest=…)` produces a working
   422	  clone at `dest`.
   423	- `GitRepo.push_ref(ref, expected_old_sha)` succeeds when the
   424	  remote ref matches `expected_old_sha`; raises `RefRefused`
   425	  when the remote has diverged.
   426	- `GitRepo.fetch_ref(ref)` updates the local ref to match
   427	  remote; returns the fetched SHA.
   428	- `GitRepo.delete_remote_ref(ref, expected_sha)` succeeds when
   429	  the remote matches; raises `RefRefused` on divergence; raises
   430	  `RefRefused` (not silent success) when the remote ref is
   431	  already gone (idempotency caveat: callers handle the
   432	  already-gone case explicitly because chapter-6 §3.4
   433	  rollback semantics distinguish "no-op" from "won the race").
   434	- Credential-helper roundtrip: drive a real `git http-backend`
   435	  via Python's `http.server` + the helper script generated by
   436	  setup-experiment's template. Assert that without the helper
   437	  the push fails 401, with the helper the push succeeds. This
   438	  proves the helper is wired correctly end-to-end at unit
   439	  speed; argv-only inspection would NOT.
   440	
   441	### Integration (`reference/packages/eden-git/tests/test_remote_integrator.py`)
   442	
   443	Drive the **public `Integrator.integrate(trial_id)` method**
   444	through each failure mode, using a real local-file remote +
   445	a monkey-patched Store:
   446	
   447	- Happy path: `integrate` succeeds → local ref + remote ref +
   448	  `trial.integrated` event all present.
   449	- Push race (step 2 fails): set the remote `trial/<id>` ref to
   450	  a different SHA before `integrate` runs. Assert: local ref
   451	  rolled back, remote untouched, no `trial.integrated` event.
   452	- Store failure after push (step 3 fails): monkeypatch
   453	  `Store.integrate_trial` to raise `DispatchError`. Assert:
   454	  remote ref deleted (compensating push), local ref deleted,
   455	  no `trial.integrated` event.
   456	- Compensating delete itself fails (step 4a fails): monkeypatch
   457	  `delete_remote_ref` to raise `GitTransportError`. Assert:
   458	  the integrator logs a critical-severity diagnostic AND the
   459	  next-startup reconciliation pass (§D.7c) cleans up the orphan
   460	  on Gitea. (Tested via a second `Integrator()` instance after
   461	  the first's failure.)
   462	
   463	### Smoke (`compose-smoke-*` extensions)
   464	
   465	Extends both `compose-smoke` and `compose-smoke-subprocess(-docker)`
   466	with one new post-quiescence assertion:
   467	
   468	```bash
   469	git ls-remote http://eden:${GITEA_REMOTE_PASSWORD}@gitea:3000/eden/${EXPERIMENT_ID}.git \
   470	    | grep -E 'refs/heads/trial/' | wc -l
   471	```
   472	
   473	≥3 (matches the existing `trial.integrated` event count
   474	assertion). Proves the remote actually has the integrated trial
   475	refs, not just the local clones.
   476	
   477	A new `compose-e2e` extension covers the chunk-9e admin
   478	work-refs GC page driving a `delete_remote_ref` against Gitea
   479	(asserts the remote ref is gone after the operator-clicks-delete
   480	flow).
   481	
   482	### `eden_git` testing scope: file-URL is enough
   483	
   484	The new unit + integration tests use `file://` URLs for the
   485	remote. We do NOT add a `pytest.mark.gitea` marker. Justification:
   486	
   487	- `git push --force-with-lease` and `git push --delete` use the
   488	  same wire protocol over file:// as over http://. The CAS
   489	  semantics are server-side (the remote's reflog), not transport-
   490	  dependent.
   491	- HTTP transport is exercised end-to-end by the smoke scripts
   492	  against the real Gitea container — that's where any
   493	  http-specific issue (auth, redirect, content-length, etc.)
   494	  surfaces.
   495	- A separate marker would split coverage and require yet another
   496	  CI service container (Gitea), with no proof that http exposes
   497	  bugs the file:// path doesn't already catch.
   498	
   499	The credential-helper unit test is the one exception: it spins
   500	up a tiny http server in-process so the auth round-trip is real,
   501	no external dependency needed.
   502	
   503	## F-T. Cutover blast-radius inventory
   504	
   505	Concrete file count from `grep -l "init_bare\|GitRepo.*bare"`
   506	across the repo (excluding READMEs):
   507	
   508	- **`reference/packages/eden-git/tests/`** (4 files —
   509	  `test_repo_branches_worktrees.py`, `test_repo_plumbing.py`,
   510	  `test_environment_isolation.py`, `conftest.py`) — these
   511	  exercise local-only `GitRepo` ops; they STAY on local-only
   512	  paths because the new ops are tested separately in
   513	  `test_remote_ops.py`.
   514	- **`reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/repo.py`** — the
   515	  module under modification. New methods land here.
   516	- **Service tests that init a local bare repo:**
   517	  - `reference/services/_common/tests/test_worktrees.py` — pure
   518	    worktree behavior, no remote — STAYS local.
   519	  - `reference/services/planner/tests/test_planner_subprocess.py`
   520	    — planner doesn't touch git refs (only proposals) — STAYS
   521	    local.
   522	  - `reference/services/implementer/tests/test_implementer_subprocess.py`,
   523	    `test_host.py` — these exercise `_run_subprocess` and
   524	    submit flows. The implementer change in §D.7 adds a single
   525	    `repo.push_ref` call after the existing `repo.create_ref`.
   526	    Tests gain a tiny bare-repo `init --bare` as the local
   527	    "remote" + assertion that `push_ref` was invoked. Net
   528	    change per test: ~5 lines.
   529	  - `reference/services/evaluator/tests/test_evaluator_subprocess.py`
   530	    — evaluator gains `fetch_ref` before worktree-add. Same
   531	    pattern: local "remote" + one-line assertion.
   532	  - `reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py`,
   533	    `test_subprocess_e2e.py` — these are the heavyweights.
   534	    Each spawns the full 5-process stack against an in-memory /
   535	    sqlite store. Adding a real local file-URL remote here
   536	    means: setUp creates `tmp_path/remote.git` as a bare repo,
   537	    the test's `seed_bare_repo` pushes to it, each spawned
   538	    service gets `--gitea-url file://<path>` instead of
   539	    `--repo-path <path>`. Net change per file: ~30 lines, no
   540	    new processes. Both tests are already `pytest.mark.e2e`,
   541	    skipped on Windows.
   542	
   543	**Total file changes for the cutover:** ~14 source files modified
   544	+ ~3 new files. Tests that don't touch a real bare repo
   545	(everything in `_common/tests/test_common.py`, web-ui non-flow
   546	tests, contracts tests, storage tests) are entirely unaffected.
   547	
   548	The "most existing tests can stay on local-only paths" claim is
   549	defensible because the **only** tests that previously exercised
   550	the implementer/evaluator/integrator flows did so against an
   551	in-process bare repo on disk; switching that bare repo to be
   552	the remote (via `file://`) and adding a tiny local working clone
   553	is mechanical — no new architecture surfaces.
   554	
   555	## Verification
   556	
   557	1. `uv run pytest -q` — full suite + new unit tests pass.
   558	2. `uv run pytest -m gitea` — integration tests pass (locally,
   559	   when a test Gitea is up).
   560	3. `bash healthcheck/smoke.sh` — host-mode smoke passes,
   561	   workers actually push to Gitea, integrator promotes via
   562	   Gitea.
   563	4. `bash healthcheck/smoke-subprocess.sh` and
   564	   `bash healthcheck/smoke-subprocess-docker.sh` — same.
   565	5. `bash healthcheck/e2e.sh` — Web UI flow still passes; Web UI
   566	   implementer module now pushes to Gitea on submit.
   567	6. CI: all 11 jobs green; no new required jobs in this chunk
   568	   (per the chunk-10d / 10e posture).
   569	
   570	## Out of scope
   571	
   572	- **Gitea HA / multi-instance.** Single Gitea, single bare-repo
   573	  there. HA is a Phase 12+ control-plane concern.
   574	- **SSH instead of HTTPS.** SSH key management is its own
   575	  follow-up; HTTPS Basic is enough for the reference.
   576	- **Gitea webhooks.** The orchestrator polls `Store` directly
   577	  for state; Gitea doesn't need to notify anyone.
   578	- **Multi-experiment Gitea.** This chunk creates ONE repo per
   579	  experiment, named after the experiment id. Coexistence of
   580	  multiple experiments on the same Gitea works naturally
   581	  (different repo names) but no special wiring.
   582	- **Branch protection inside Gitea.** The reference relies on
   583	  CAS at the git layer (`--force-with-lease`); a Gitea-side
   584	  branch protection rule would be redundant.
   585	- **Updating branch protection on the GitHub side** to require
   586	  any new CI job. Same posture as 10c/10d/10e/follow-up-A.
   587	
   588	## Risks
   589	
   590	- **Local ref + remote push atomicity.** Between the local
   591	  `create_ref` and the remote `push_ref` there's a window
   592	  where the local ref exists but the remote doesn't. If the
   593	  worker host crashes there, the next startup's `git fetch`
   594	  gives it a stale local view. Mitigation: at startup, after
   595	  fetch, trim any local-only `work/*` refs that aren't on
   596	  the remote (they're orphans by definition under the
   597	  full-cutover model).
   598	- **Credential exposure.** The credential-helper script lives
   599	  on the host filesystem with mode 0644 (mounted ro into the
   600	  worker). Any process on the host with read access can grab
   601	  the password. This matches the existing soft-isolation
   602	  posture; we document it in §7 of the reference-binding
   603	  chapter alongside the existing DooD caveats.
   604	- **Push-rejected during integration.** If two integrators race
   605	  and one's push gets `RefRefused`, the loser must run the
   606	  chapter-6 §3.4 compensating delete on its local trial ref
   607	  AND ensure no `trial.integrated` event was emitted for that
   608	  trial yet. The fix is structural: emit `trial.integrated`
   609	  only AFTER the push succeeds; before then, only the local
   610	  ref exists and the loser's compensating delete is local-only.
   611	- **Gitea downtime.** Workers exit on Gitea-unreachable; compose
   612	  restarts them. Brief Gitea downtime should not lose data
   613	  (workers just re-fetch when Gitea comes back). Long downtime
   614	  is operator concern.
   615	- **Setup-experiment ordering.** Gitea provisioning depends on
   616	  Gitea being healthy, which depends on `compose up`. So
   617	  `setup-experiment.sh` either (a) runs `compose up gitea --wait`
   618	  itself before provisioning, or (b) defers provisioning until
   619	  the operator runs `compose up`. Cleanest: option (a) — the
   620	  script already runs blob-init synchronously, this is the
   621	  same shape.

